text.tspan: Working Product = Requirements
The work product is an output of a Project. They are the lowest level of
project work that are individually estimated, budgeted, assigned,
executed, measured and controlled. Work products include both
tangible things such as infrastructure
installations and intangible things such as presentations.
The following are illustrative examples.
Requirements
Functional and non-functional requirements. In many cases, requirements are collected and refined
by a team of analysts assigned to the project and delivered for sign off.
Market Research - Market Research study may be included as a work product fro a product development project,
Design – Software apps for completed climate controlled
Technical Component – The coding for relay sensors or transaction
Engineering Design- The design of container(s) layout
Installation – Installation of equipment such as the heating, ventilation and air conditioning systems for containers
Connection _ The connection of a containers electrical system to the grid
Inspection – scheduled safety, product, equipment and ? inspection
Testing - An testing cycle that produces analysis/data/documentation reports and defects
Data- Input/ output of compilation of all data and inventories
Procurement – Procuring materials for manufacturing processor
Training - workshops/sessions for users of new bamboo snow system
Sales Collateral(s) – brochure for bamboo snow product(s)
Overview: Work Product
Type – Project management
Definition (1)
The smallest unit of project output that is estimated
budgeted, assigned, executed, measured and controlled
Definition (2)
Tangible and Intangible outputs of projections
Related – Deliverable
Concepts = Project Management
